The paper deals with graph pattern matching, which is a common problem in database systems (cs.DB). The focus is on temporal graphs, which are graphs that change over time, making it relevant to the sub-category of temporal data management (cs.SI). The proposed approach involves filtering potential matches based on structure and time, which is a problem that falls under the sub-category of graph algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also presents experiments with real datasets, which is a common practice in machine learning and data mining (cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
